It’s believed the pair had been travelling from the province to Gauteng. JOHANNESBURG - Police said they arrested two men for stealing fuel worth more than R3 million from a Transnet station in Warden, in the Free State. It’s believed the pair had been travelling from the province to Gauteng. Hawks spokesperson captain Lloyd Ramovha said the suspects were handcuffed after a tip-off. “The four tankers, laden with stolen diesel and petrol, were intercepted near a farm. The pair, both Zimbabwean nationals, will appear in court to face charges of theft and damaging essential infrastructure.”